Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
ENGROSSED
HOUSE BILL No. 1242
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
education.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 20-19-3-41.3 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
2 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 41.3. (a) The department shall
4 prepare a report compiling statewide data on school corporations
5 and charter schools. The report must include the following
6 information:
7 (1) The total number of school corporations and charter
8 schools in Indiana disaggregated by:
9 (A) county population;
10 (B) the number of school corporations and charter schools
11 per county; and
12 (C) the number of students enrolled in each school
13 corporation and charter school.
14 (2) Data regarding chronic absenteeism rates, performance on
15 the statewide assessment program, performance on the
16 determinant evaluation of reading skills approved by the state
17 board, and teacher salaries, disaggregated by:
EH 1242—LS 6896/DI 143

2
1 (A) county population;
2 (B) the number of school corporations and charter schools
3 per county; and
4 (C) the number of students enrolled in each school
5 corporation and charter school.
6 (3) Recommendations to:
7 (A) increase school corporation and charter school
8 administrative efficiencies;
9 (B) reduce school corporation and charter school
10 administrative costs; and
11 (C) improve student outcomes.
12 (b) Not later than December 1, 2026, the department shall, in an
13 electronic format under IC 5-14-6, submit the report prepared
14 under subsection (a) to the:
15 (1) legislative council; and
16 (2) interim study committee on education established by
17 IC 2-5-1.3-4.
18 (c) This section expires December 31, 2026.
