COMMITTEE REPORT
Mr. Speaker: Your Committee on Education, to which was referred
House Bill 1242, has had the same under consideration and begs leave
to report the same back to the House with the recommendation that said
bill be amended as follows:
Page 1, line 4, delete "corporations." and insert "corporations and
charter schools.".
Page 1, line 6, after "corporations" insert "and charter schools".
Page 1, line 9, after "corporations" insert "and charter schools".
Page 1, line 10, after "school" insert "corporation and charter
school.".
Page 1, delete line 11, begin a new line block indented and insert:
"(2) Data regarding chronic absenteeism rates, performance
on the statewide assessment program, performance on the
determinant evaluation of reading skills approved by the state
board, and teacher salaries, disaggregated by:
(A) county population;
(B) the number of school corporations and charter schools
per county; and
(C) the number of students enrolled in each school
corporation and charter school.".
Page 1, line 12, delete "(2)" and insert "(3)".
Page 1, line 13, after "corporation" insert "and charter school".
Page 1, delete line 14.
Page 1, line 15, after "corporation" insert "and charter school".
Page 1, line 15, delete "costs." and insert "costs; and
(C) improve student outcomes.".
Page 1, line 16, delete "September" and insert "December".
and when so amended that said bill do pass.
(Reference is to HB 1242 as introduced.)
